 discussion questions and recommendations for further reading. The closing chapter reveals a nascent "ethic of transnational and intercultural research" growing out of contributors' lessons learned and generous reflections. Anyone interested in or planning to undertake a transnational or intercultural project can benefit from these storied case studies, and as a result, this collection contributes to moving the field forward as it strives to promote more ethically aware and responsive research.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCommunication of technical informationxResearchvCase studies. 0aIntercultural communicationxResearchvCase studies. 0aResearchxInternational cooperationvCase studies. 0aResearchxMoral and ethical aspectsvCase studies. 4aCommunication : Technical Communication. 7aTechnology & Engineering / Technical Writing.2bisacsh1 aAmaya, Bea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDurão, Rosário, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHijazi, Nabila, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHopton, Sarah Beth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIlunga, Yvan Yenda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLaura, Pigozzi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLongo, Bernadette, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLongo, Bernadette, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLópez-Léon, Ricardo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatheson, Breeanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMattson, Kyle, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoura, Joana, econtributor.4ctb4https://i